#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:8
msgid "Highlights"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:10 ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:35
msgid ""
"If a `.Future` contains an exception but that exception is never examined"
" or re-raised (e.g. by yielding the `.Future`), a stack trace will be "
"logged when the `.Future` is garbage-collected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:13 ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:55
msgid ""
"New class `tornado.gen.WaitIterator` provides a way to iterate over "
"``Futures`` in the order they resolve."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:15 ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:189
msgid ""
"The `tornado.websocket` module now supports compression via the "
"\"permessage-deflate\" extension.  Override "
"`.WebSocketHandler.get_compression_options` to enable on the server side,"
" and use the ``compression_options`` keyword argument to "
"`.websocket_connect` on the client side."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:20
msgid ""
"When the appropriate packages are installed, it is possible to yield "
"`asyncio.Future` or Twisted ``Defered`` objects in Tornado coroutines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:24
msgid "Backwards-compatibility notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:26 ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:75
msgid ""
"`.HTTPServer` now calls ``start_request`` with the correct arguments.  "
"This change is backwards-incompatible, afffecting any application which "
"implemented `.HTTPServerConnectionDelegate` by following the example of "
"`.Application` instead of the documented method signatures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:33
msgid "`tornado.concurrent`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:38
msgid "`.Future` now catches and logs exceptions in its callbacks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:41
msgid "``tornado.curl_httpclient``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:43
msgid ""
"``tornado.curl_httpclient`` now supports request bodies for ``PATCH`` and"
" custom methods."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:45
msgid ""
"``tornado.curl_httpclient`` now supports resubmitting bodies after "
"following redirects for methods other than ``POST``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:47
msgid ""
"``curl_httpclient`` now runs the streaming and header callbacks on the "
"IOLoop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:49
msgid ""
"``tornado.curl_httpclient`` now uses its own logger for debug output so "
"it can be filtered more easily."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:53
msgid "`tornado.gen`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:57
msgid ""
"When the `~functools.singledispatch` library is available (standard on "
"Python 3.4, available via ``pip install singledispatch`` on older "
"versions), the `.convert_yielded` function can be used to make other "
"kinds of objects yieldable in coroutines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:61
msgid ""
"New function `tornado.gen.sleep` is a coroutine-friendly analogue to "
"`time.sleep`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:63
msgid "`.gen.engine` now correctly captures the stack context for its callbacks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:66
msgid "`tornado.httpclient`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:68
msgid ""
"`tornado.httpclient.HTTPRequest` accepts a new argument "
"``raise_error=False`` to suppress the default behavior of raising an "
"error for non-200 response codes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:73
msgid "`tornado.httpserver`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:80
msgid ""
"`.HTTPServer` now tolerates extra newlines which are sometimes inserted "
"between requests on keep-alive connections."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:82
msgid ""
"`.HTTPServer` can now use keep-alive connections after a request with a "
"chunked body."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:84
msgid ""
"`.HTTPServer` now always reports ``HTTP/1.1`` instead of echoing the "
"request version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:88
msgid "`tornado.httputil`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:90
msgid ""
"New function `tornado.httputil.split_host_and_port` for parsing the "
"``netloc`` portion of URLs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:92
msgid ""
"The ``context`` argument to `.HTTPServerRequest` is now optional, and if "
"a context is supplied the ``remote_ip`` attribute is also optional."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:94
msgid ""
"`.HTTPServerRequest.body` is now always a byte string (previously the "
"default empty body would be a unicode string on python 3)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:96
msgid ""
"Header parsing now works correctly when newline-like unicode characters "
"are present."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:98
msgid "Header parsing again supports both CRLF and bare LF line separators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:99
msgid ""
"Malformed ``multipart/form-data`` bodies will always be logged quietly "
"instead of raising an unhandled exception; previously the behavior was "
"inconsistent depending on the exact error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:104
msgid "`tornado.ioloop`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:106
msgid ""
"The ``kqueue`` and ``select`` IOLoop implementations now report "
"writeability correctly, fixing flow control in IOStream."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:108
msgid ""
"When a new `.IOLoop` is created, it automatically becomes \"current\" for"
" the thread if there is not already a current instance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:110
msgid ""
"New method `.PeriodicCallback.is_running` can be used to see whether the "
"`.PeriodicCallback` has been started."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:114
msgid "`tornado.iostream`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:116
msgid ""
"`.IOStream.start_tls` now uses the ``server_hostname`` parameter for "
"certificate validation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:118
msgid ""
"`.SSLIOStream` will no longer consume 100% CPU after certain error "
"conditions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:119
msgid ""
"`.SSLIOStream` no longer logs ``EBADF`` errors during the handshake as "
"they can result from nmap scans in certain modes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:123
msgid "`tornado.options`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:125
msgid ""
"`~tornado.options.parse_config_file` now always decodes the config file "
"as utf8 on Python 3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:127
msgid ""
"`tornado.options.define` more accurately finds the module defining the "
"option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:131
msgid "``tornado.platform.asyncio``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:133
msgid ""
"It is now possible to yield ``asyncio.Future`` objects in coroutines when"
" the `~functools.singledispatch` library is available and "
"``tornado.platform.asyncio`` has been imported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:136
msgid ""
"New methods `tornado.platform.asyncio.to_tornado_future` and "
"`~tornado.platform.asyncio.to_asyncio_future` convert between the two "
"libraries' `.Future` classes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:141
msgid "``tornado.platform.twisted``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:143
msgid ""
"It is now possible to yield ``Deferred`` objects in coroutines when the "
"`~functools.singledispatch` library is available and "
"``tornado.platform.twisted`` has been imported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:148
msgid "`tornado.tcpclient`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:150
msgid ""
"`.TCPClient` will no longer raise an exception due to an ill-timed "
"timeout."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:154
msgid "`tornado.tcpserver`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:156
msgid "`.TCPServer` no longer ignores its ``read_chunk_size`` argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:159
msgid "`tornado.testing`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:161
msgid ""
"`.AsyncTestCase` has better support for multiple exceptions. Previously "
"it would silently swallow all but the last; now it raises the first and "
"logs all the rest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:164
msgid ""
"`.AsyncTestCase` now cleans up `.Subprocess` state on ``tearDown`` when "
"necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:168
msgid "`tornado.web`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:170
msgid ""
"The `.asynchronous` decorator now understands `concurrent.futures.Future`"
" in addition to `tornado.concurrent.Future`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:172
msgid ""
"`.StaticFileHandler` no longer logs a stack trace if the connection is "
"closed while sending the file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:174
msgid ""
"`.RequestHandler.send_error` now supports a ``reason`` keyword argument, "
"similar to `tornado.web.HTTPError`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:176
msgid "`.RequestHandler.locale` now has a property setter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:177
msgid ""
"`.Application.add_handlers` hostname matching now works correctly with "
"IPv6 literals."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:179
msgid ""
"Redirects for the `.Application` ``default_host`` setting now match the "
"request protocol instead of redirecting HTTPS to HTTP."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:181
msgid ""
"Malformed ``_xsrf`` cookies are now ignored instead of causing uncaught "
"exceptions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:183
msgid ""
"``Application.start_request`` now has the same signature as "
"`.HTTPServerConnectionDelegate.start_request`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:187
msgid "`tornado.websocket`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:194
msgid ""
"`.WebSocketHandler` no longer logs stack traces when the connection is "
"closed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:196
msgid ""
"`.WebSocketHandler.open` now accepts ``*args, **kw`` for consistency with"
" ``RequestHandler.get`` and related methods."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:198
msgid "The ``Sec-WebSocket-Version`` header now includes all supported versions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v4.1.0.rst:199
msgid ""
"`.websocket_connect` now has a ``on_message_callback`` keyword argument "
"for callback-style use without ``read_message()``."
msgstr ""

